<br>
About pets against uber mobs, hmm.  Anyone still have the parsed log info from the Sleepers Tomb raid?  I was looking for that the other day and couldn't find it among the posts.  I think it showed pure melees and maybe rangers doing more damage than the epic pet, but the epic pet did more than paladins, shadow knights and bards.  I think the log also showed the damage output of non epic pets, but I just don't remember.<br>
<br>
If you want to use a pet against Trakanon, summon him before the fight while others are buffing.  Guard him at a spot where repop isn't going to happen till a few minutes after the fight has started.  Once you get up there, summon companion the pet and tell it to attack Trak.  Right after you tell your pet to attack, also tell it to follow you or guard that new spot so he doesn't go walking back to his old spot and aggro juggs onto you.  The main concern doing this is if you get hit by an AE before you get summon companion off.  Just an idea for those that do want to use a pet against Trakanon.<br>
<br>
I'd like to try and dispell this myth that our water pets are immune to poison.  They are very resistant, but not totally immune.  I've seen a necro land a poison based dot on my water pet in a duel.  I've seen Trakanon poison my water pet with his breath.  I'm not certain about this one, but I seem to remember Sev landing his poison based stun on my water pet before.  Just because water can and does frequently resist poison doesn't mean he is immune.  It just takes one poison spell to land to disprove his immunity.  I'm not sure if air or earth are immune to anything since I haven't actually sat down with someone and tested it, but I'm doubtful.  At the moment the only pet I know is immune to an element is our fire pet.<br>
